name: Support Patients
desc: Health care (also health-care or healthcare) is the maintenance or improvement of health via the prevention, diagnosis, treatment, recovery, or cure of disease, illness, injury, and other physical and mental impairments in people. Health care is delivered by health professionals and allied health fields.

name: Mental Therapy
desc: The health and safety of every person is our top priority. Like all emergencies, response is most successful when it is locally executed, state managed and federally supported. We are partnering with the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to address needs across the healthcare community.

name: Support Patients
desc: Health care systems are organizations established to meet the health needs of targeted populations. According to the World Health Organization (WHO), a well-functioning health care system requires a financing mechanism, a well-trained and adequately paid workforce, reliable information on which to base.
